   "Situation: A potential client decided to work with another company\nDistorted Thought: I failed our company & myself\nRational Response: Did I? I am merely a small part of this company and shouldn't take the sole responsibility for its successes and failures",
   "Situation: A potential client decided to work with another company\nDistorted Thought: I failed our company & myself\nRational Response: I'm a small part of this company and shouldn't take the sole responsibility for its successes and failures",
   'Situation: A potential client decided to work with another company.\nDistorted Thought: I failed our company & myself.\nRational Response: I am not a failure because a client made a different decision than I wanted them to. I am doing the best work I can, which is why I feel so invested in this outcome. If one client decision is enough to make me feel like a complete failure, I will take that as a sign that I need to be more kind to myself.',
   'Situation: A potential client decided to work with another company.\nDistorted Thought: I failed our company & myself.\nRational Response: I cannot control my potential clients. It sounds like we may not have been a good fit and that is okay! If this is really bothering me, I can reach out to the client for feedback or talk to my supervisor about what happened.',
   "Situation: I applied for a promotion but was told I haven't shown the necessary ambition yet. This happened at work where I always go the extra mile, stay late, and even work when I'm not being paid. I feel like the response to my request for a promotion was inaccurate and that I am being taken advantage of because nothing I could do is enough. I was denied the promotion by the department head who is a woman that seems to always talk down to and be rude to men at the company.\nDistorted Thought: I felt as if my talents and efforts were being unrecognized by the company yet they are perfectly happy to accept all of my hard work, just not pay me what I deserve for it.\nRational Response: Maybe there was a different candidate who deserved the promotion more than I did. I should ask the company for some feedback. Maybe it is not so personal, maybe there was just somebody who deserved it more.",
   "Situation: Recently I found out that one of my coworkers with who I work closely, organized a party and I wasn't invited to the party.\nDistorted Thought: I felt left out and singled out in the office and wondered if the person had a personal grudge against me.\nRational Response: It does not feel good to be left out but that does not mean it was personal",
   "Situation: Recently I found out that one of my coworkers with who I work closely, organized a party and I wasn't invited to the party.\nDistorted Thought: I felt left out and singled out in the office and wondered if the person had a personal grudge against me.\nRational Response: There may be many reasons this person did not invite me to their party.",
   "Situation: Someone criticized the way I dealt with a patient saying that I was too short tempered with them.\nDistorted Thought: I felt the criticism was unfair because they didn't take into account the entire situation, especially considering how the patient was behaving towards me.\nRational Response: I know the details of this situation and was the person involved so my response style is for me to decide",
