   "Situation: Everyone is mean to me\nDistorted Thought: I hate everyone\nRational Response: When people are mean to me, it makes me feel angry. I can focus on what I can control about the situation and let go of what I can't control.",
   'Situation: I tried to make friends with people but they kept ignoring me.\nDistorted Thought: I am not interesting\nRational Response: It takes time to meet new people and to integrate into a new social group where everyone knows each other. I just need to keep trying my best and finding more outlets to interact with people with similar interests to me.',
   "Situation: I tried to make friends with people but they kept ignoring me.\nDistorted Thought: I am not interesting\nRational Response: Other people may not be ignoring me because they don't find me interesting. They may just already be busy and have a lot of friends.",
   "Situation: i celebrated a past holiday by myself\nDistorted Thought: why don't i have friends? why am i not social? SIGH!\nRational Response: I didnt reach out to anybody to see if they wanted to get together for the holiday. I am sure if I had reached out, people would have been available. Next time, I should plan ahead.",
   "Situation: I tried to make friends with people but they kept ignoring me.\nDistorted Thought: I am not interesting\nRational Response: Other people may not be ignoring me because they don't find me interesting. They may just already be busy and have a lot of friends.",
   "Situation: The host of a party is giving me one-word responses when I try to talk to them\nDistorted Thought: I feel like an outcast\nRational Response: I'm feeling like an outcast and I'm unable to talk to people. But let's see if there are other fun things to do at the party",
   "Situation: The host of a party is giving me one-word responses when I try to talk to them\nDistorted Thought: I feel like an outcast\nRational Response: I'm feeling like an outcast, but so do many others",
   "Situation: The host of a party is giving me one-word responses when I try to talk to them\nDistorted Thought: I feel like an outcast\nRational Response: Just because I feel like an outcast, doesn't mean I must be an outcast",
   "Situation: Everyone is mean to me\nDistorted Thought: I hate everyone\nRational Response: When people are mean to me, it makes me feel angry. I can focus on what I can control about the situation and let go of what I can't control.",
   "Situation: People around me do not need my presence\nDistorted Thought: I'm worthless\nRational Response: My self worth doesn't come from how many other people need me. It's okay to take care of myself and do the things that are important to me.",
   "Situation: Lately, I've been increasingly noticing being removed from people. I've always kept a distance with my family, but now my friends don't care about me and it oppresses me. Many of my acquaintances have a soulmate, a lover who will support them in a difficult period of life, and just make them happy. I've never had a relationship, because of this I feel different and it's harder for me to find a common language, but I just don't want to rush things. In addition, I have been suffering from overeating for the past couple of weeks and since the beginning of the Christmas holidays my sleep has increased to 12-14 hours a day, which I also consider harmful. I've never had this and I don't know how to deal with it. Politics is also putting pressure on me. I feel uncomfortable and don't know what to do\nDistorted Thought: I need relationship\nRational Response: It's normal and human to feel lonely. I don't need another person to complete me. I will find love someday, but in the meantime I can enjoy what I have in the moment.",
   'Situation: Everyone is mean to me\nDistorted Thought: I hate everyone\nRational Response: Some of the people in my life are mean to me. I would like to find friends who treat me well and appreciate the good things about me',
