   "Situation: I received a subpar quiz score in a class.\nDistorted Thought: I should have studied harder, or more efficiently.\nRational Response: that was a hard test. i'll study more efficiently next time.",
   "Situation: I made very good English presentation but I got nervous because of the amount of people and I forgot my text\nDistorted Thought: I'm scared to present in front of other people and I panic\nRational Response: I am allowing one bad experience to cloud my judgement on my ability to present in front of other people.  Just because I panicked today doesn't mean I will have that reaction every time.",
