   "Situation: I am unable to write the essay\nDistorted Thought: My laptop is crap! If only I had a better laptop, I could have been better at writing\nRational Response: Not true! I shouldn't blame my laptop for not being able to write",
   "Situation: Having problems coming up with words to write essay.\nDistorted Thought: I will get a bad grade.\nRational Response: I'm feeling anxious about this assignment. I can use skills to calm myself, try my best on the essay, ask for any appropriate help, and whatever grade I get I will know that I tried my hardest.",
   "Situation: Having problems coming up with words to write essay.\nDistorted Thought: I will get a bad grade.\nRational Response: I'm having trouble writing this essay but will do my best.",
   "Situation: It's so hard to study effectively and it takes all the time and energy I have. And then I still don't feel prepared.\nDistorted Thought: I'm so behind and i'm so afraid of the terrible grades I will recieve. I can't do anything right\nRational Response: I don't know what's going to happen. All I can do is prepare myself.",
