   'Situation: Last week I made a special dinner at my house for my family to enjoy but I overcooked the food.\nDistorted Thought: after 30 years since I first started learning how to cook I am still ruining meals.\nRational Response: I made a mistake of overcooking the food, it happens to everyone. It is difficult to prepare meals perfectly, every time.',
   "Situation: I did badly in a writing contest I entered. I did not final.\nDistorted Thought: I am a bad writer.\nRational Response: Most people who enter a contest don't win. I know I can become a great writer and will keep trying.",
   "Situation: I was given a solo for the church play.  At practice when it came time for me to sing, my voice cracked and I lost the solo.\nDistorted Thought: I can't sing.\nRational Response: I have been singing a lot and was not taking enough time to rest and prepare, and as a result, I faced some consequences. In the future, I will try to take better care of my voice so I can do the things I love!",
   "Situation: I was given a solo for the church play.  At practice when it came time for me to sing, my voice cracked and I lost the solo.\nDistorted Thought: I can't sing.\nRational Response: Everyone makes mistakes. I know I can sing because I was given a solo. I can keep practicing and be more prepared for next time.",
   "Situation: I cant work out what my real personality is because my opinions and moods change all the time and Its like I change into different personalities kind of but its not different conciousmesses its just i dont know how to explain it but I think im insane because I dont know much about who I am because who I am changes and it can change very fast, is this normal?\nDistorted Thought: i have no stable identity and I dont know why or if its normal\nRational Response: It can be scary to feel like I have no identity, but I do have one whether or not I'm aware of it.",
   "Situation: I cant work out what my real personality is because my opinions and moods change all the time and Its like I change into different personalities kind of but its not different conciousmesses its just i dont know how to explain it but I think im insane because I dont know much about who I am because who I am changes and it can change very fast, is this normal?\nDistorted Thought: i have no stable identity and I dont know why or if its normal\nRational Response: It's ok to not know my exact identity. That is normal.",
