   "Situation: I'm worthless\nDistorted Thought: My parents left me at the store\nRational Response: My parents mistreated me this time, but it probably doesn't have anything to do with me. They  made a mistake, but I can forgive them if they make positive changes and show that they care.",
   "Situation: That I’m hopeless, and it would be better if I were dead\nDistorted Thought: My dad is going to leave me for his grandfather who abused me as a kid, and my dad knows about it.\nRational Response: It's messed up that my dad would choose my abuser over me. I know there are other people who will support me. I can do this",
   "Situation: That I’m hopeless, and it would be better if I were dead\nDistorted Thought: My dad is going to leave me for his grandfather who abused me as a kid, and my dad knows about it.\nRational Response: It's sad that my dad is unable to see why his choices are wrong. His choices are not a reflection of my worth.",
   "Situation: My parent's fight\nDistorted Thought: Their constant disagreements and arguments\nRational Response: It's normal to be afraid when my parents are constantly fighting. It's not a good environment for a kid to be in, but I can reach out for help. It's not my fault my parents fight.",
