   "Situation: My spouse got a new gaming console and spends most of his free time playing video games.\nDistorted Thought: I am not good enough for him.\nRational Response: My spouse is doing something he really enjoys, I'm glad he is having fun! I will ask him if we can schedule a date later this week to get some quality time together.",
   'Situation: I was on the phone with my boyfriend and he got a call on the other line. I assumed it was another girl calling him.\nDistorted Thought: I am not good enough.\nRational Response: Instead of making assumptions, I can talk to my boyfriend and express my feelings of insecurity.',
   "Situation: I had a breakup\nDistorted Thought: I am the cause of the breakup\nRational Response: It's normal to feel sad and guilty about a breakup. Sometimes relationships just don't work out. It doesn't have to be anyone's fault.",
   "Situation: I had a breakup\nDistorted Thought: I am the cause of the breakup\nRational Response: I shouldn't blame only me for my breakup. We both were equal partners in our relationship",
   "Situation: My partner left me.\nDistorted Thought: I did something wrong\nRational Response: I'm feeling hurt that my partner left and I need to process how we got to this point.",
   'Situation: My partner was visiting her daughter, who was having surgery.  I got annoyed with her on the phone because she was being distracted.\nDistorted Thought: I wanted her to pay attention and not interrupt me.\nRational Response: My partner should be there for her daughter. I can call her later to check in on how she is feeling, rather than making myself the priority.',
   "Situation: My partner was visiting her daughter, who was having surgery.  I got annoyed with her on the phone because she was being distracted.\nDistorted Thought: I wanted her to pay attention and not interrupt me.\nRational Response: My partner was probably distracted because her daughter is having surgery. Her daughter should be her priority right now and I shouldn't take it so personally.",
   "Situation: My girlfriend was distracted by other men at the gym.\nDistorted Thought: I'm not attractive enough.\nRational Response: People are attracted to other people without taking action on it or thinking less of their monogamous partners",
   "Situation: I am quite fond of a coworker and decide to talk to them. I offer up the idea that it might be fun to go out together sometime, and they respond with the fact they are too busy.\nDistorted Thought: I'm not attractive or have a good enough personality.\nRational Response: My feeling are hurt after getting rejected like that. It could be true that they are too busy or maybe there are other reasons they don't want to go out with me. I can't know for sure but I will get over this and find a good match for me.",
   "Situation: I ask out a co-worker who I became fond of recently but was turned down.\nDistorted Thought: I'm not good enough for her.\nRational Response: Getting rejected hurts. There are many reasons she could have said no. I'll recover and eventually find the person who is right for me.",
   "Situation: My husband got two tickets to a Bruins game the other day and rather than asking me if I wanted to go with him he invited a friend.\nDistorted Thought: My husband doesn't want to spend time with me.\nRational Response: I spend a lot of time with my partner and maybe he wants some connecting time with a friend. I have a healthy relationship with my partner.",
   "Situation: I was talking to my husband about something that happened to me that day.  He kept interrupting and talking over me.  I got up and left the room.\nDistorted Thought: My husband was being a jerk and not listening to me.\nRational Response: I didn't appreciate my husband's behavior. I should talk with him so he knows how I feel when he interrupts or talks over me.",
   'Situation: I was talking to my husband about something that happened to me that day.  He kept interrupting and talking over me.  I got up and left the room.\nDistorted Thought: My husband was being a jerk and not listening to me.\nRational Response: While it was not kind of my husband to interrupt me, he may have had something else on his mind and not have been aware that he was interrupting.',
   "Situation: My girlfriend was ignoring me for a while.\nDistorted Thought: She didn't like me anymore.\nRational Response: If my girlfriend doesn't like me anymore, I trust that she will tell me that and not just ignore me. Guessing at what others are thinking is not fair to either one of us.",
   "Situation: My girlfriend was ignoring me for a while.\nDistorted Thought: She didn't like me anymore.\nRational Response: My girlfriend has not responded, but I should be patient and not jump to conclusions about what this means until I talk to her",
   "Situation: My husband and his friends are always speaking Spanish in front of me and I cannot understand anything\nDistorted Thought: they are saying things in front of me that they don't want me to know or understand\nRational Response: There are many reasons why native Spanish speakers may want to speak Spanish to each other that are not about me.",
   "Situation: I invited a co-worker out and they turned me down\nDistorted Thought: They will never want to go out with me\nRational Response: I'm sure their response was not about me, this coworker must have other things going on.",
   "Situation: My girlfriend was sad that I wanted to go out with my friends, and started a fight.\nDistorted Thought: Why can't I have fun? Why must I stay home all the time?\nRational Response: I wonder if there's something I'm missing in our dynamic. It's important to talk about how she feels when I go out, and is there something else that's not working in our relationship.",
   "Situation: My girlfriend was sad that I wanted to go out with my friends, and started a fight.\nDistorted Thought: Why can't I have fun? Why must I stay home all the time?\nRational Response: My girlfriend is telling me that she's feeling sad that I'm going out, I wonder if she's feeling left out or lonely. We should talk about how she's feeling.",
   "Situation: my spouse is bugging me\nDistorted Thought: mistreated me\nRational Response: It's important to communicate my feelings in a constructive way. I can set boundaries with my spouse.",
   "Situation: I'm a failure\nDistorted Thought: I made my husband feel bad and depressed I made the house so bleak\nRational Response: I'm capable of making things better. I can make the house more inviting and cheerful.",
