   "Situation: My relationship of 2 years ended out of nowhere, constantly stressed about my job, i ever feel like be worth it to another person or to my friends unless they need something.\nDistorted Thought: I don’t feel like I’m worth it.\nRational Response: It's okay to feel discouraged sometimes. I have made it this far, and I know I will be able to keep going.",
   "Situation: I ask out a co-worker who I became fond of recently but was turned down.\nDistorted Thought: I won't find someone I can be with\nRational Response: I'm sad I don't get to be with that person but I will eventually find the right match.",
   "Situation: My wife, asked me very kindly, to finally clean the bathroom shower in our bathroom, and I got upset by this.\nDistorted Thought: I'm busy doing something else, it's not like I haven't tried to get to that chore!\nRational Response: I am feeling overwhelmed with everything I need to do. I have neglected cleaning the shower for a couple of weeks. I should budget the time to complete that tomorrow and get it finished.",
   "Situation: My wife, asked me very kindly, to finally clean the bathroom shower in our bathroom, and I got upset by this.\nDistorted Thought: I'm busy doing something else, it's not like I haven't tried to get to that chore!\nRational Response: She is not necessarily telling me that I am not working hard enough on other tasks and demands in our lives. She is communicating her need for support with one specific task. I will work on fulfilling my commitments when I commit to doing so.",
   "Situation: I ask out a co-worker who I became fond of recently but was turned down.\nDistorted Thought: I'm not good enough for her.\nRational Response: I feel sad that she turned me down but maybe this is for the best.",
   "Situation: My girlfriend came home later than usual after work and didn't bother to call and let me know or answer the phone when I called to check on her. She acted like it was not big deal after she came home.\nDistorted Thought: My girlfriend is hiding something from me.\nRational Response: I am feeling hurt by her actions and can discuss that with her rather than try to analyze her behavior",
   "Situation: My first boyfriend and I broke up 6 years ago\nDistorted Thought: My partner will leave me if my depression doesn't go away soon.\nRational Response: Many people with depression are still able to have healthy relationships. We can work through this challenge together.",
