   "Situation: The guy I'm dating went home early one night and I got upset because I thought it meant he didn't want to see me anymore, but I was wrong.\nDistorted Thought: I guess he doesn't like me anymore\nRational Response: I didn't know why he did that, and what I thought wasn't correct, but that doesn't mean he doesn't like me anymore.",
   "Situation: My boyfriend went to visit his son and wound up spending the entire day with his son and his son's mother while ignoring my phone calls.\nDistorted Thought: I thought he was cheating on me\nRational Response: It is good my boyfriend is spending time with his son. He will probably call me when he has some free time.",
   "Situation: My boyfriend went to visit his son and wound up spending the entire day with his son and his son's mother while ignoring my phone calls.\nDistorted Thought: I thought he was cheating on me\nRational Response: My boyfriend spending time with his son is important to him. Seeing his son and his ex does not mean he is cheating on me, it is a part of co-parenting and my boyfriend still loves me.",
